The article is a transcript of a speech given at the White House to celebrate the 2023 National Student Poets. The speaker expresses their appreciation for poetry and its ability to provide comfort and express emotions. They thank the student poets from St. Louis, Salt Lake City, Brooklyn, Norman, Oklahoma, and Lakeland, Florida for their contributions. The speaker emphasizes the importance of poetry in a fast-paced world and encourages the poets to continue sharing their talents. They also acknowledge the support of the poets' families, teachers, and communities. The article concludes with a thank you message to everyone involved in the event.